The paper focuses on utilizing contextual information to improve the performance of event detection, which is a task commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed model also involves machine learning techniques, such as dynamic memory network (DMN), which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the model's performance, which can be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on a specific dataset, which can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
